OL,7,FWahed, which described itself as an
OL,8,Finvestment platform allowing consumers
OL,9,Fwho were predominantly Muslim to
OL,10,Finvest in a manner which aligned with
OL,11,Ftheir faith and values, said it often
OL,12,Fused the term "Riba", which was an
OL,13,FArabic word that meant "excess" and
OL,14,Fwas commonly used to describe the
OL,15,Fprohibition of interest under Islamic
OL,16,Flaw.
