OL,7,FWahed told the ASA that it
OL,8,Facknowledged that currencies were a
OL,9,Fsymbol of national identity but
OL,10,Fbelieved the burning of banknotes was
OL,11,Fnot offensive and was portrayed in
OL,12,Fpopular culture, such as film and TV.
OL,14,FIt said the burning of banknotes
OL,15,Fwithin the ads was designed to be a
OL,16,F"powerful visual illustration" that
OL,17,Fmoney was akin to "going up in flames"
OL,18,Fwhen inflation grew faster than the
OL,19,Frate of savings.
